@gigicomidinhas

Taste: 5; Atmosphere: 4.4; Service: 4.5. Visits: 5+.

Quick take: one of best, if not the best, tasting coffee/espresso in Tokyo. If you are into coffee, this is place is a must.

Notes of interest:
Cash only (makes up for it with lower prices);
Limited options for drinks w/ milk and milk alternatives;
7 roasts to choose from: light to dark;
Limited seating: 3 seats inside and 4 outside;
Beans roasted in shop.

Can you be a great barista AND great roaster?   Apparently, yes.

The mastermind of Murrma validates this with his remarkable roasting and perfect pouring.

Reading through the comments multiple people have made the claim that this is the best coffee shop in Tokyo, and this would be hard to dispute. This really is a very special place. I often will travel 45 minutes out of my way to visit. (Recently everyday.)

Owner is super friendly, and extremely passionate about coffee and creating a place where people can enjoy a wonderful coffee experience.

Murrma coffee exemplifies a passionate artisan pursuing his life’s love, and we, the fortunate patrons, can enjoy the remarkable results.

